<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="211" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 184/66</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Secretary of the Commission to Negotiate
                                Peace</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJC1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to Mr.
                                    <persName corresp="#p_BWC1" type="to">William C.
                                    Bullitt</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                                </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-23">December
                                    23, 1918</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>In pursuance of a memorandum submitted by Dr. <persName corresp="#p_MSE1">Mezes</persName> to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">Grew</persName>
                            and approved by the Commission, you have been appointed Chief of the
                            division entitled Current Intelligence Summaries, one of the divisions
                            of that section of the American Commission to Negotiate Peace entitled
                            Territorial, Economic and Political Intelligence.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>